   Lepeletier, 1841 and X (Koptortosoma) pubescens Spinola, 1838 were
   moderately common, those of X. (Copoxyla) armeniaca Warncke, 1982, X.
   (Ancylocopa) parviceps Morawitz 1895, X. (Xylocopa) varentzowi Morawitz,
   1895, X. (Ctenoxylocopa) fenestrata (Fabricius, 1798), and X
   (Proxylocopa) rufa Friese, 1901 occur in restricted areas within
   Anatolia and could be accepted as rare species. Update floral
   associations and geographical distribution were included for each
   species. Field studies revealed that Xylocopa species, particularly X.
   valga, X. violacea, X. iris and X. olivieri are valuable pollinators of
   some cultivated plants, such as apple (Malus domestica Borkh), pear
