Month = {{JUL-SEP}},
Abstract = {{Influence of pollinators on seed production and quality of carrot and
   sweet pepper in a greenhouse
   Pollination is a fundamental process for the perpetuation of various
   plant species, and the development of fruits and seeds is directly
   related to the pollination of flowers. Thus, the aim of this study was
   to assess the influence of pollinators on seed production and quality of
   carrot and sweet pepper under greenhouse conditions. In the carrot
   study, plants were grown in cages, and the following treatments were
   used: pollination with Arapua (Trigona spinipes) bees, Jatai
