Abstract = {{Floral visitors of the homoploid hybrid species, Iris nelsonii
   (Abbeville Red Iris), were observed and identified in order to determine
   whether Abbeville Red Iris flowers are visited by similar floral
   visitors as its progenitor Iris species. The most common floral visitors
   to Abbeville Red Iris flowers were Archilochus colubris (Ruby-throated
   Hummingbird), which were also largely successful in transferring a
   pollen dye-analogue between Abbeville Red Iris flowers. Other floral
